338 // \todo THIS IS REALLY BAD. NEED TO MOVE THIS AND RELATED FUNCTIONALITY OUT OF HERE
339 template <typename T>
340 void MotionPlanningFrame::waitForAction(const T& action, const ros::NodeHandle& node_handle,
341  const ros::Duration& wait_for_server, const std::string& name)
342 {
343  ROS_DEBUG("Waiting for MoveGroup action server (%s)...", name.c_str());
344 
345  // in case ROS time is published, wait for the time data to arrive
346  ros::Time start_time = ros::Time::now();
347  while (start_time == ros::Time::now())
348  {
349  ros::WallDuration(0.01).sleep();
350  ros::spinOnce();
351  }
352 
353  // wait for the server (and spin as needed)
354  if (wait_for_server == ros::Duration(0, 0))
355  {
356  // wait forever until action server connects
357  while (node_handle.ok() && !action->isServerConnected())
358  {
359  ros::WallDuration(0.02).sleep();
360  ros::spinOnce();
361  }
362  }
363  else
364  {
365  // wait for a limited amount of non-simulated time
366  ros::WallTime final_time = ros::WallTime::now() + ros::WallDuration(wait_for_server.toSec());
367  while (node_handle.ok() && !action->isServerConnected() && final_time > ros::WallTime::now())
368  {
369  ros::WallDuration(0.02).sleep();
370  ros::spinOnce();
371  }
372  }
373 
374  if (!action->isServerConnected())
375  throw std::runtime_error("Unable to connect to move_group action server within allotted time");
376  else
377  ROS_DEBUG("Connected to '%s'", name.c_str());
378 };
